      <p>
        More than ever, ‘work’ and what it means is changing for both employees and employers and with this comes a need for a different approach to recruitment that answers the needs of both the individual and the business.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our philosophy is simple, but one that is borne from our own experiences working within recruitment consultancy over the last 20 years.  Candidates need the right business and businesses need the right people. That may sound obvious but in fact is forgotten all too often when recruitment becomes transactional. Getting the match between the two parties perfected is what we have built our reputations on. This means is that we won’t put forward candidates for a role who view it is simply a wage packet. And we won’t work with businesses who view their people just as lines on a balance sheet. Work, and the employer/employee relationship, have to be based on more than these binary factors for it to truly bear fruit.
      </p>
      <p>
        Whether you are an individual or a business, we will ask you lots of questions and listen actively to the answers so that we understand completely what you are looking for. Sometimes the simple act of asking these questions helps provide clarity and focus to your search where perhaps it was lacking before.
      </p>
